    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI installed neovim from Flathub according to [documentation](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/INSTALL.md#flatpak), but launching always fails with:\r\n```\r\n/app/bin/nvim: error while loading shared libraries: libluv.so.1: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't know whether previous version was having the same behavior, as I was using version from fedora repos.\r\n\r\nAlso, I'm not sure whether that build is official, but it has unverified badge on Flathub, so if someone creates broken builds, which could hurt nvim's reputation, I would report the app to Flathub.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nflatpak install flathub io.neovim.nvim\r\nflatpak run io.neovim.nvim\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLaunching neovim\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, there is no flatpak vim, just gvim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 40\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal 3.50.1 for GNOME 45 or empty tty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nflatpak",
